## coomments in c :- there are two types of comment in c 
    single line comments:- // comments 
    multiline comments:- /* comments */

why use comments as we know we write code as instruction like this:

    #include <stdio.h>

    int main() {
    int a = 12;
    printf("The value of a is %d\n", a);
    return 0;
    }  
    
    in this no on understand which lines means what and what exactly its doing this is a code that do something and goves the output there is no doubt but this visibal term no one easily understand 

    forr that reason we type comment in normal english or any human understandable language that simply defines the meaning of that line of code 
    so, 
            int main() { } // this is an integer type function that starts and inside that function all the code is going to written 

            that comment defines the meaning if that code.
        

## to run a c program in vs code :-
    gcc filename.c -o program 
        * gcc - we know computer understand 0 and 1 so gcc calls GNU compiler collection so it cinverts the human lang into binary 
        * filename.c this is the file name that we wnat to translate into binary and .c defines that its an c file 
        * -o -> this is a flog or can say switch that stand for output 
        * prpgram this give a name by using it u get the output like it can be anything not only program 
    ./program 

    instead of this ./program you can give any name like gcc filename.c -o manav or dog and while running just ./manav, ./dog
